993int
994gf100_grctx_mmio_data(struct gf100_grctx *info, u32 size, u32 align, u32 access)
995{
996 if (info->data) {
997 info->buffer[info->buffer_nr] = round_up(info->addr, align);
998 info->addr = info->buffer[info->buffer_nr] + size;
999 info->data->size = size;
1000 info->data->align = align;
1001 info->data->access = access;
1002 info->data++;
1003 return info->buffer_nr++;
1004 }
1005 return -1;
1006}

1008void
1009gf100_grctx_mmio_item(struct gf100_grctx *info, u32 addr, u32 data,
1010 int shift, int buffer)
1011{
1012 struct nvkm_device *device = info->gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
1013 if (info->data) {
1014 if (shift >= 0) {
1015 info->mmio->addr = addr;
1016 info->mmio->data = data;
1017 info->mmio->shift = shift;
1018 info->mmio->buffer = buffer;
1019 if (buffer >= 0)
1020 data |= info->buffer[buffer] >> shift;
1021 info->mmio++;
1022 } else
1023 return;
1024 } else {
1025 if (buffer >= 0)
1026 return;
1027 }
1028
1029 nvkm_wr32(device, addr, data);

1148void
1149gf100_grctx_generate_r418bb8(struct gf100_gr *gr)
1150{
1151 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
1152 u32 data[6] = {}, data2[2] = {};
1153 u8 tpcnr[GPC_MAX];
1154 u8 shift, ntpcv;
1155 int gpc, tpc, i;
1156
1157 /* calculate first set of magics */
1158 memcpy(tpcnr, gr->tpc_nr, sizeof(gr->tpc_nr));
1159
1160 gpc = -1;
1161 for (tpc = 0; tpc < gr->tpc_total; tpc++) {
1162 do {
1163 gpc = (gpc + 1) % gr->gpc_nr;
1164 } while (!tpcnr[gpc]);
1165 tpcnr[gpc]--;
1166
1167 data[tpc / 6] |= gpc << ((tpc % 6) * 5);
1168 }
1169
1170 for (; tpc < 32; tpc++)
1171 data[tpc / 6] |= 7 << ((tpc % 6) * 5);
1172
1173 /* and the second... */
1174 shift = 0;
1175 ntpcv = gr->tpc_total;
1176 while (!(ntpcv & (1 << 4))) {
1177 ntpcv <<= 1;
1178 shift++;
1179 }
1180
1181 data2[0] = (ntpcv << 16);
1182 data2[0] |= (shift << 21);
1183 data2[0] |= (((1 << (0 + 5)) % ntpcv) << 24);
1184 for (i = 1; i < 7; i++)
1185 data2[1] |= ((1 << (i + 5)) % ntpcv) << ((i - 1) * 5);
1186
1187 /* GPC_BROADCAST */
1188 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x418bb8, (gr->tpc_total << 8) |
1189 gr->magic_not_rop_nr);
1190 for (i = 0; i < 6; i++)
1191 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x418b08 + (i * 4), data[i]);
1192
1193 /* GPC_BROADCAST.TP_BROADCAST */
1194 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x419bd0, (gr->tpc_total << 8) |
1195 gr->magic_not_rop_nr | data2[0]);
1196 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x419be4, data2[1]);
1197 for (i = 0; i < 6; i++)
1198 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x419b00 + (i * 4), data[i]);
1199
1200 /* UNK78xx */
1201 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4078bc, (gr->tpc_total << 8) |
1202 gr->magic_not_rop_nr);
1203 for (i = 0; i < 6; i++)
1204 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40780c + (i * 4), data[i]);
1205}

1207void
1208gf100_grctx_generate_r406800(struct gf100_gr *gr)
1209{
1210 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
1211 u64 tpc_mask = 0, tpc_set = 0;
1212 u8 tpcnr[GPC_MAX];
1213 int gpc, tpc;
1214 int i, a, b;
1215
1216 memcpy(tpcnr, gr->tpc_nr, sizeof(gr->tpc_nr));
1217 for (gpc = 0; gpc < gr->gpc_nr; gpc++)
1218 tpc_mask |= ((1ULL << gr->tpc_nr[gpc]) - 1) << (gpc * 8);
1219
1220 for (i = 0, gpc = -1, b = -1; i < 32; i++) {
1221 a = (i * (gr->tpc_total - 1)) / 32;
1222 if (a != b) {
1223 b = a;
1224 do {
1225 gpc = (gpc + 1) % gr->gpc_nr;
1226 } while (!tpcnr[gpc]);
1227 tpc = gr->tpc_nr[gpc] - tpcnr[gpc]--;
1228
1229 tpc_set |= 1ULL << ((gpc * 8) + tpc);
1230 }
1231
1232 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x406800 + (i * 0x20), lower_32_bits(tpc_set));
1233 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x406c00 + (i * 0x20), lower_32_bits(tpc_set ^ tpc_mask));
1234 if (gr->gpc_nr > 4) {
1235 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x406804 + (i * 0x20), upper_32_bits(tpc_set));
1236 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x406c04 + (i * 0x20), upper_32_bits(tpc_set ^ tpc_mask));
1237 }
1238 }

1274int
1275gf100_grctx_generate(struct gf100_gr *gr)
1276{
1277 const struct gf100_grctx_func *grctx = gr->func->grctx;
1278 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
1279 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
1280 struct nvkm_memory *chan;
1281 struct gf100_grctx info;
1282 int ret, i;
1283 u64 addr;
1284
1285 /* allocate memory to for a "channel", which we'll use to generate
1286 * the default context values
1287 */
1288 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST, 0x80000 + gr->size,
1289 0x1000, true, &chan);
1290 if (ret) {
1291 nvkm_error(subdev, "failed to allocate chan memory, %d\n", ret);
1292 return ret;
1293 }
1294
1295 addr = nvkm_memory_addr(chan);
1296
1297 /* PGD pointer */
1298 nvkm_kmap(chan);
1299 nvkm_wo32(chan, 0x0200, lower_32_bits(addr + 0x1000));
1300 nvkm_wo32(chan, 0x0204, upper_32_bits(addr + 0x1000));
1301 nvkm_wo32(chan, 0x0208, 0xffffffff);
1302 nvkm_wo32(chan, 0x020c, 0x000000ff);
1303
1304 /* PGT[0] pointer */
1305 nvkm_wo32(chan, 0x1000, 0x00000000);
1306 nvkm_wo32(chan, 0x1004, 0x00000001 | (addr + 0x2000) >> 8);
1307
1308 /* identity-map the whole "channel" into its own vm */
1309 for (i = 0; i < nvkm_memory_size(chan) / 4096; i++) {
1310 u64 addr = ((nvkm_memory_addr(chan) + (i * 4096)) >> 8) | 1;
1311 nvkm_wo32(chan, 0x2000 + (i * 8), lower_32_bits(addr));
1312 nvkm_wo32(chan, 0x2004 + (i * 8), upper_32_bits(addr));
1313 }
1314
1315 /* context pointer (virt) */
1316 nvkm_wo32(chan, 0x0210, 0x00080004);
1317 nvkm_wo32(chan, 0x0214, 0x00000000);
1318 nvkm_done(chan);
1319
1320 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100cb8, (addr + 0x1000) >> 8);
1321 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100cbc, 0x80000001);
1322 nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
1323 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x100c80) & 0x00008000)
1324 break;
1325 );
1326
1327 /* setup default state for mmio list construction */
1328 info.gr = gr;
1329 info.data = gr->mmio_data;
1330 info.mmio = gr->mmio_list;
1331 info.addr = 0x2000 + (i * 8);
1332 info.buffer_nr = 0;
1333
1334 /* make channel current */
1335 if (gr->firmware) {
1336 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409840, 0x00000030);
1337 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409500, 0x80000000 | addr >> 12);
1338 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409504, 0x00000003);
1339 nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
1340 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409800) & 0x00000010)
1341 break;
1342 );
1343
1344 nvkm_kmap(chan);
1345 nvkm_wo32(chan, 0x8001c, 1);
1346 nvkm_wo32(chan, 0x80020, 0);
1347 nvkm_wo32(chan, 0x80028, 0);
1348 nvkm_wo32(chan, 0x8002c, 0);
1349 nvkm_done(chan);
1350 } else {
1351 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409840, 0x80000000);
1352 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409500, 0x80000000 | addr >> 12);
1353 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409504, 0x00000001);
1354 nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
1355 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409800) & 0x80000000)
1356 break;
1357 );
1358 }
1359
1360 grctx->main(gr, &info);
1361
1362 /* trigger a context unload by unsetting the "next channel valid" bit
1363 * and faking a context switch interrupt
1364 */
1365 nvkm_mask(device, 0x409b04, 0x80000000, 0x00000000);
1366 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409000, 0x00000100);
1367 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
1368 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409b00) & 0x80000000))
1369 break;
1370 ) < 0) {
1371 ret = -EBUSY;
1372 goto done;
1373 }
1374
1375 gr->data = kmalloc(gr->size, GFP_KERNEL);
1376 if (gr->data) {
1377 nvkm_kmap(chan);
1378 for (i = 0; i < gr->size; i += 4)
1379 gr->data[i / 4] = nvkm_ro32(chan, 0x80000 + i);
1380 nvkm_done(chan);
1381 ret = 0;
1382 } else {
1383 ret = -ENOMEM;
1384 }
1385
1386done:
1387 nvkm_memory_del(&chan);
1388 return ret;
1389}
